# SEO sync rule

When you change **user-visible page content** in the portfolio app, check whether SEO metadata still matches. Update SEO **in the same change** when it does not. Do not leave stale titles, descriptions, or missing prerender/sitemap entries.

## Source of truth

| What | Where |
|------|--------|
| Home title & description | `packages/portfolio/src/constants/site.js` → `HOME_PAGE_META` |
| Project title, summary, OG image | `packages/portfolio/src/constants/projects.js` → `title`, `description`, optional `ogImage` |
| Route → meta mapping | `packages/portfolio/src/utils/getRouteMeta.js` |
| Head tag rendering | `packages/portfolio/src/utils/documentMeta.js` |
| JSON-LD structured data | `packages/portfolio/src/utils/structuredData.js` + `packages/portfolio/src/constants/site.js` (`SITE_ROLE`, `SITE_LINKEDIN`, `SITE_GITHUB`, `SITE_TELEGRAM`) |
| Client head sync | `packages/portfolio/src/components/RouteMeta.jsx` |
| Prerender routes | `packages/portfolio/src/constants/projects.js` → `PRERENDER_ROUTES` |
| Crawl files | `packages/portfolio/scripts/generate-crawl-files.mjs` → `public/robots.txt`, `public/sitemap.xml` (from `PRERENDER_ROUTES` + `VITE_SITE_URL`) |
| Canonical base URL | `VITE_SITE_URL` in env; fallback in `site.js` |

Project pages derive `<title>`, `meta description`, Open Graph, Twitter, and canonical URL from `projects.js`. Home page meta is **not** auto-derived from `Landing.jsx`; update `HOME_PAGE_META` explicitly.

## When to update SEO

**Update metadata when you change any of these:**

- Hero headline or role/tagline on the landing page → `HOME_PAGE_META.title` and/or `description` (keep aligned with visible copy; descriptions ~150–160 chars, factual, no lorem ipsum)
- Landing bio or intro paragraph that summarizes the site → `HOME_PAGE_META.description`
- Project name → `projects.js` `title` (also drives `<title>` and `og:title`)
- Project card or case-study summary → `projects.js` `description`
- Project hero/lead text on `ProjectPage` → same `description` if it is the page summary
- Project slug or URL → `slug`, `href`, and confirm `PRERENDER_ROUTES` still correct
- New indexable route (e.g. new `/work/:slug`) → add to `PROJECTS`, ensure `PRERENDER_ROUTES` includes it, add to `public/sitemap.xml` when that file exists
- New share/preview image → `public/` asset + `ogImage` on the project or update `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE` in `site.js`
- Page becomes non-indexable (dev-only, gated) → exclude from `PRERENDER_ROUTES` / sitemap; use `noindex` when robots/meta infra exists

**Usually no SEO change needed:**

- Layout, styling, or animation-only edits
- TOC, section headings, or body copy **below** the project summary (unless the summary itself changed)
- Component refactors that do not change rendered text
- Resources app content (passcode-gated; must stay non-indexable)

## Checklist (run before finishing a content edit)

1. Does visible copy still match `HOME_PAGE_META` or the project's `title` / `description`?
2. Are titles concise and unique? Format: `{Page} | Maxim Sokolov` for projects; home uses `HOME_PAGE_META.title`. Never use em dashes in titles or descriptions.
3. Is `description` a real summary (not placeholder), suitable for search and social previews?
4. If a route was added or removed, is `PRERENDER_ROUTES` updated? Re-run build so `sitemap.xml` regenerates.
5. If metadata changed, run `npm run build` in `packages/portfolio` and confirm prerendered HTML in `dist/` has correct `<head>` tags.

## Structured data

When JSON-LD exists, update `Person` / `CreativeWork` in `structuredData.js` when name, role, bio, project title, or summary changes. Keep `SITE_LINKEDIN`, `SITE_GITHUB`, `SITE_TELEGRAM` in `site.js` current with profile URLs. Schema must cite the same facts as visible copy and meta tags.

## Resources app

Do not index `packages/resources`. Never copy its content into portfolio SEO metadata.
